<br>
I personally don't believe our class could be, or ever will be with mythics current view of a merc, a FOTM class. When people roll a FOTM, they roll for a meaning that is highly valuable. Savage do extreme damage with his positionals, Bezerker use to do incredible damage almost anywhere, mana enchanters are just freakin' uber.. You catch my drift. Each one has something that really turns the tide of battle. That's what people want. To make a difference. Not be a damage add for an arms, pally or reaver. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :| --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/indifferent.gif ALT=":|"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Though, our realm counter-part, the Bladenaster, has been getting some real attention from the crowd. Some even say FOTM! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  While I don't personally think they do any better than befor (don't play one - from a one on one pov), they must be appealing due to their anti-crit specialty.<br>
<br>
In the over-all picture, though, there's really not many tanks. It's usually a nice trade of caster/tanks, but recently has been much more caster-ish. I believe tanks feel casters are better off (having played my brothers newly reached 50 fire wizard once or twice, I tend to agree) and new 20/30s make it an appealing choice. While casters feel tanks are better off, but don't want to roll them (would you rather be the protector, or protecty who kills things?).<br>
<br>
Well see what happens. To make absalutly sure that you don't get labeled FOTM, go out and RvR as much as you're willing to. People will know your name and (hopefully) start thinking &quot;Now that merc knows what he's doing&quot;. Surprizingly, it doesn't take too long to get a reputation goin'. Trick is making it a nice one. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
Lothire - 50 Mercenary<br>
Darktendrils - 4x Necromancer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosimond@lighttanksofdaoc>Rosimond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#000000>(8/6/03 7:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=309.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well I didn't notice...</span><hr size=1> On the subject of RvR, my little merc spent her first real night in Emain duoing with a Sorc ... both of us 45th. We had a blast and I made 5 realm levels (up to 2L1 now). Travelling with your own mezzer never hurts of course. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Ran into an orange con blademaster with IP and purge and he gave us no trouble at all. Also took down several small groups of orange and yellow cons. We died to a group of 4 with a RR5 and RR6 in it which made sense to me. Considering how well she's doing at this point I think she'll just fine at 50. I don't see her as a &quot;damage add&quot; in the least. My damage suits me just fine.<br>
<br>
but I do think that it takes more than &quot;doing well&quot; to be a FOTM. People who play those want something overpowered, not something that just does the job it's intended to do. <br>
